<br>
2. Mission types differ.  High DPS groups will like slaughter missions.  Assassination missions are likely gonna be most popular cause once you kill enugh to spawn boss, you can just pacify through and cap him.  With rescue missions, you gotta clear all the mobs en route to target, and then take time to lead him out.  Collection missions are likely to be least popular due to fact that collectables distribution is finicky at best.  If most of them are way deep, you are screwed.<br>
<br>
3. Any dungeon has a chance to spawn some 'named' mobs that will drop cool loot.  Yesterday, a 'Forgotten Yun Sorcerer' yielded a real nice 47/45 2HB on a Guk crawl.  <br>
<br>
4. Lower type augs (the +6 variety) are random rare drops.  So far, I've seen at least 2 drop on each crawl.<br>
<br>
5. 'Objects' come in two flavors: I call em containers and surprises.  Containers you can inspect, and try to unlock.  Surprises you simply whack and hope for the best.  Bitten victims in Mistmoore, cursed guktans in Guk and creaking crates in Ruj are the surprises.  For the most part, we got a mana boost from whacking those, but on one occasion, poking a cursed guktan spawned 3 nasty slimes.<br>
<br>
6. tradeskills: smiths rejoice, there's now a new 188-212 skillup route.  Temper components can drop/be foraged in dungeons, and everything else is storebought.  212-250 is still a bear, but at least ther's gonna be a tad less competition for swirling/wailing/shrieking.<br>
<br>
7. LDoN takes a different mentality.  Casters who are used to their horsies better watch their aggro, or they won't be able to med.  Also, if you wannt be on time, you generally bring fight to mobs, not sit and wait for the puller to bring you something. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bregalad Alcarin</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, High Elf Coercer, Xev &lt;Legends of Westwood&gt;<br>
